1
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,360
I want to go home so bad!

2
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:54,680
Why don't we play a little game
to open up to each other?

3
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:56,600
Yay!

4
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,520
We can just come up
with the questions ourselves.

5
00:00:58,520 --> 00:00:59,560
Who wants to start first?

6
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:02,560
Have you guys...
ever had a secret crush on a coworker?

7
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:05,400
Come here, let me do it for you.

8
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:06,800
Thank you.

9
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,720
I’ve never felt this happy before.

10
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:10,960
Chai, I'm cold.

11
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:15,360
Once we go back...
will things be weird between us?

12
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:20,800
Glamorous Airline is here
to take everyone back home!

13
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:30,200
I want to go home so bad!

14
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:32,360
My body is completely covered in rashes.

15
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:33,520
My immune system is shot.

16
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:34,960
My body is shutting down.

17
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:38,960
I think we’re all gonna catch
a disease and die on this island.

18
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,640
Hey!

19
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,760
But we have a doctor right here!

20
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:46,200
Doctor, please examine us.

21
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,200
Find out what kind of disease we have.

22
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,760
You want me to do
a medical checkup right now?

23
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:50,640
Yes!

24
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:51,320
For what?

25
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:52,080
Wait, what?

26
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:53,560
Even if I diagnose you,
I can't treat it anyway.

27
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,600
You useless doctor!

28
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,160
Oh, I am useful.

29
00:01:56,160 --> 00:01:58,160
Have you guys seen your faces lately?

30
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:01,800
Here, let me take care of your skin.

31
00:02:01,800 --> 00:02:03,160
At least when you die...

32
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:04,760
...you’ll be a beautiful corpse.

33
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:08,120
So, how does my face look?

34
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:10,200
It's sagging all the way to the floor.

35
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:13,560
For this, you need an 800-shot
Ulthere program right away.

36
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,120
I haven't slept well in days.

37
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,040
How bad is my condition?

38
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:16,800
Like a zombie.

39
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,360
Botox is your only hope.

40
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,520
And some under-eye fillers
will make it better.

41
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:23,320
What about me?
Mosquitoes bit my entire face and body.

42
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,840
I’m covered in marks.

43
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,400
Then the V-Face program it is!

44
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,840
600 shots of Oligie...

45
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:29,960
...plus another 400 shots of
UltraTransformer.

46
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,920
Oh, Doctor.
But for someone like me...

47
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:33,840
...the most beautiful girl in the airline...

48
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,120
...I don't really have any skin issues.

49
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:37,040
Just a few minor...

50
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:38,240
...bear claw marks.

51
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:41,120
My face is full of holes now!

52
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,120
Gorgeous!

53
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:43,720
See? I told you so.

54
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,600
With a face like that,
you might as well not have a head.

55
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,320
We need to use needles
to subcise the scar tissue.

56
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:49,720
And then Sculptre.

57
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:51,240
Lots and lots of that.

58
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:54,120
Holy shit,
he just roasted the hell out of me.

59
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,120
And right now, everyone...

60
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:58,440
...it's the 7/7 flash sale!

61
00:02:58,440 --> 00:03:00,920
The glowing-skin package
is at an amazing price.

62
00:03:00,920 --> 00:03:01,760
Just sign right here.

63
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:02,720
Great price!

64
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:07,160
Sign it, come on.

65
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:11,080
Oh, I totally forgot about this guy.

66
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:13,360
Doctor, is there any procedure...

67
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,920
...that can make her love me back?

68
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:16,360
Huh?

69
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:19,440
I knew it!
Kreetha has a secret crush on me!

70
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:20,800
No, no!

71
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,320
See? I knew it, Doctor!

72
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:23,240
He said no.

73
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:24,160
Yeah, because he's in denial!

74
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,800
Honestly, he likes me.

75
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:28,200
And it's because he ate this mushroom.

76
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,200
Whoa!

77
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:32,480
Whoa!

78
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:36,960
This mushroom...looks just like
a Bear-Eared Mushroom.

79
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,680
It’s extremely rare.

80
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:42,880
If you guys knew
how to consume it properly...

81
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:46,280
...it tastes just like
premium sake or fine wine.

82
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:48,000
Oh, that's fabulous!

83
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,000
That's fabulous, Doctor!

84
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,800
It tastes good, right?

85
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,600
Tid-Gift, let me feed you.

86
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,520
No thanks,
I’m already tripping.

87
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:01,120
Everyone,
since we’re partying together...

88
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:04,360
...why don't we play a little game
to open up to each other?

89
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:07,000
Great!

90
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,760
Okay, for the questions...

91
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:10,320
...we can just come up
with them ourselves.

92
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:11,600
As for the penalties...

93
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:13,600
...we’ll randomly
draw cards from this deck.

94
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:17,240
Who wants to start first?

95
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,520
Then for the first question...

96
00:04:18,520 --> 00:04:19,840
Huh?

97
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:23,840
Have you ever been in
a relationship with a big age gap?

98
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:30,200
Spin the bottle!
And that person answers.

99
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:37,960
You know, guys...

100
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:39,080
...we’ve never known anything about...

101
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:40,880
...Ms. Petchgam Ploy’s love life at all.

102
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,320
Tell us about it!

103
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:44,400
I choose the penalty.

104
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:48,400
What?

105
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:53,080
What is this?
"Dance to your favorite song."

106
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,600
I can do that.

107
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,800
Everyone, clap along!

108
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:01,880
One, two...

109
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:02,840
...three!

110
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:04,640
The Kinnaree happily plays in the water.

111
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:07,120
She stands up and sees a wet bear.

112
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,680
She grabs the bear and shakes it,
shakes it.

113
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:11,200
But the wind doesn't blow,
so the bear is still wet.

114
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,800
The Kinnaree then asks the angel...

115
00:05:12,800 --> 00:05:15,120
...to make the wind blow,
so the bear won't be wet anymore.

116
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:16,560
The angel takes pity on the Kinnaree...

117
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:19,080
...blows three times,
and the bear is no longer wet.

118
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:22,080
Wet, wet, wet, wet!

119
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:26,120
I don't think this is a penalty,
she clearly loves dancing.

120
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,520
How could you tell?

121
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,160
Next! Next!

122
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,880
Let's keep playing the game.

123
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:34,960
Then my question is...
have you guys...

124
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,960
...ever had a secret crush
on a coworker?

125
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:42,680
Okay, spin!

126
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:52,480
Ms. Tid-Gift, you're up!

127
00:05:53,360 --> 00:05:54,800
I choose Truth.

128
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:56,960
I'm always straightforward.

129
00:05:58,280 --> 00:05:59,560
Yes, I have.

130
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,200
Gift, bitch!

131
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:04,560
Do you have a secret crush on me?

132
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,840
I think you, Ms. Tid-Gift...

133
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:09,200
...have a secret crush on me,
don't you?

134
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,360
Looking at your coworkers...

135
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:13,560
...not a single one of them
is even likable.

136
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:14,800
Excuse me, Doctor.

137
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,600
Huh?

138
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,640
One.

139
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:19,240
I have never worked with you.

140
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,560
Two.

141
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:21,840
I don't consider you a friend.

142
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:23,040
Oh!

143
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:23,920
Three.

144
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,720
Before you try to act like
a picky bachelor...

145
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,840
...try being hot first
before you start picking.

146
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:31,800
Oh damn! Tid-Gift scores ten!

147
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,840
Doctor Yep scores zero!

148
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,040
Shall we keep going then?

149
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:34,680
Yes, yes, yes!

150
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,400
Sounds good.

151
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:37,280
It's the pretty girl's turn to spin now.

152
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,400
Uh-oh!

153
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,880
Oh my!

154
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,920
The question is...

155
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,640
...who do you have
a secret crush on?

156
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:57,160
Then, Sky, I choose Dare.

157
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,760
I'll take the penalty.

158
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:00,360
Oh, no way, no way!

159
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,120
What? No way!

160
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,520
Yeah, that's cheating!

161
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:03,360
I already said I choose Dare.

162
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,480
I'll take the penalty.

163
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,840
Fine, fine, fine.
The penalty is...

164
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:14,520
...turn around and kiss the cheek
of the person on your left.

165
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:17,520
The person on your left.

166
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:26,280
Kiss her! Kiss her! Kiss her!

167
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:28,600
I can't do that.

168
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,080
It's disrespectful to her.

169
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:33,200
Hey, why are you trying to act
like a gentleman right now, Kree?

170
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:36,200
Do you like someone in this circle or what?
That's why you can't answer?

171
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,680
Just give me a kiss,
it's just a game.

172
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,360
Wow, she's got guts.

173
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:47,360
I didn't think he'd actually do it.

174
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:49,360
Look how blushing he is.

175
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:55,960
Hey, Chai!

176
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:57,040
Something is wriggling on my leg.

177
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,440
Can you check it for me?

178
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,440
Holy shit, a snake!

179
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:08,280
I can handle a bear,
but a cobra is where I draw the line!

180
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:09,560
Stay still!

181
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,360
What's the big deal?
It's just a snake.

182
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:12,960
Sky, watch out!

183
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,760
Don't be scared, guys.

184
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,760
I can speak snake language!

185
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,800
We’re safe now.

186
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:31,840
It's fine.

187
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:34,880
See?

188
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:44,800
What is it?
Why did you call me here?

189
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:48,520
Everything is a sign from the universe.

190
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:55,320
Oh god, the reason
I could speak to a snake...

191
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:57,400
...must be because of
the Bear-Eared Mushroom.

192
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:01,680
Have you ever wondered why
you were born without a soulmate?

193
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:03,800
Because of my past karma.

194
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:05,440
Every fortune teller tells me
the exact same thing.

195
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:09,360
It's because you haven't found
someone of your own species yet.

196
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,560
And what species am I?

197
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:11,600
Khieo Sawoei mango.

198
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,360
Nam Dok Mai mango.

199
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:12,960
Rad mango.

200
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:15,360
Stop kidding around,
I’m not playing.

201
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:17,960
You need to find someone
who was born a snake just like you.

202
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,600
Only then will you find your soulmate.

203
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:23,240
I knew it!
No wonder I could never get a boyfriend.

204
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:26,760
So from now on, my goal...

205
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:28,880
...is to become a snake's wife, right?

206
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:30,840
Yes. Here are the signs to look for.

207
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:32,760
One, sharp and handsome features.

208
00:09:32,760 --> 00:09:34,600
Two, filthy rich.

209
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:37,240
Three, he hits on you first.

210
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,840
Fabulous!

211
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,880
Just hearing that gives me goosebumps.

212
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:42,720
I will definitely become a snake's wife!

213
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:48,600
One baht to watch,
nothing beats a snake's wife!

214
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,480
You can stroke her,
you can touch her.

215
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:54,240
You can stroke her, you can touch her,
but don't poke her hole with a stick!

216
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:56,240
Poke her hole, poke her hole!

217
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,120
It’s getting pretty chilly, isn't it?

218
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:10,880
Tonight, I’ll hold you close.

219
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:13,680
Hey, are you tripping right now?

220
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:16,680
Yeah, I’m still tripping.

221
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:20,640
I think this is way stronger than wine.

222
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:23,040
Stronger than sake, even.

223
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:25,040
My head is spinning.

224
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:31,120
The stars are so beautiful tonight,
aren't they?

225
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,880
The moon is beautiful too.

226
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:35,160
So beautiful.

227
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,800
But not as beautiful as you.

228
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:43,680
Are you crazy?
What’s wrong with you?

229
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:45,320
Seriously...

230
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:48,160
The person at the office
you said you liked...

231
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:49,480
...who is it?

232
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,200
Why do you want to know?

233
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:55,680
Anyone would have a crush on
someone at the office at some point, right?

234
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,560
Father...

235
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,240
Father, where are you?

236
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:12,960
Father, please, where are you?

237
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:13,960
Father...

238
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:20,560
Hey, what are you doing?

239
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:21,520
It's none of your concern!

240
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:23,360
Oh, that’s harsh.

241
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,760
I was actually just looking for my father.

242
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:26,760
What on earth is going on?

243
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,200
You guys,

244
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:32,840
I think I just unlocked
a new life level.

245
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:37,520
Mr. Snake told me that
in my past life...

246
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,680
...I was born a snake.

247
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:40,680
Huh?

248
00:11:40,680 --> 00:11:42,160
The reason I don't have a boyfriend...

249
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:44,560
...is just because I haven't met someone
who was born a snake like me yet.

250
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,920
Full Nakee goddess mode now, huh?

251
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:49,320
This is straight up a drama plot.

252
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,400
Go ahead and mock it.

253
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,200
You won't die a peaceful death for sure.

254
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,960
What if us getting stranded on this island...

255
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:58,080
...is actually a sign from the universe?

256
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:04,520
You two ate way
too many Bear-Eared Mushrooms...

257
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:05,640
...and now you're hallucinating.

258
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:08,080
Watch out or you'll go crazy
before you even get a boyfriend.

259
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:11,160
What about you, Doctor?
Do you have a partner?

260
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:12,800
Do I look like I have a partner?

261
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:14,040
Not at all.

262
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:16,440
And you don't look like
you have friends either.

263
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:22,040
Oh please, the three of us,
who actually has a partner?

264
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,040
None of us do.

265
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:25,000
Well, Doctor...

266
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,280
...what should we do...

267
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:30,280
...to kill this crippling loneliness?

268
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,080
Crippling loneliness?

269
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,600
How about this? I think...

270
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:37,400
...we should do some kind of activity...

271
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,120
...with a rhythm or something.

272
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,880
I can tolerate a lot of things from you guys...

273
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:43,720
It might feel a little thrilling.

274
00:12:44,520 --> 00:12:46,040
Whoa!

275
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,920
You guys go do that yourselves.

276
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:49,840
Leave me out of this,
I'm not getting involved.

277
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:51,280
What?
Where are you running off to?

278
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:52,520
Come do it with us!

279
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:54,120
No way!

280
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:55,720
All-New, come on!

281
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:56,600
Hey!

282
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,960
Come here.

283
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:59,080
Don't mess with me!

284
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,080
Come on!

285
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,640
You're this cute.

286
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:08,520
You should find someone
to take care of you already.

287
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:17,160
Chai, I'm cold.

288
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:26,720
I don't think you need
to freeze your eggs anymore.

289
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:29,120
I'll just put mine in your eggs instead.

290
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,840
That’s naughty!

291
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,040
Oh!

292
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:34,120
What's that wriggling?

293
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,800
Is it a snake?

294
00:13:37,240 --> 00:13:39,160
Must be highly venomous too.

295
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:08,520
Oh, you didn't bring a towel?

296
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:11,040
If you don't mind,
you can use mine first.

297
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:14,120
Oh, I can just reuse my old towel.

298
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:15,040
It's fine, thanks.

299
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:16,280
Why would you use an old towel?

300
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:18,280
