374
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:35,280
Did you get hooked?

375
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:37,920
But we have to use protection, you know.

376
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:40,000
Whoa! Stop, stop, stop!

377
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:43,840
We don't want a little
Bear-Eared Mushroom baby...

378
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:45,200
...popping out, do we?

379
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:47,280
Hey, are you crazy?

380
00:18:47,280 --> 00:18:48,960
There's no way
we’d hit the jackpot like that.

381
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:49,960
Is that so?

382
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:56,840
Gift...

383
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:58,480
This is kind of weird.

384
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:00,480
Once we leave this place...

385
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,600
...will things be weird between us?

386
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,840
Of course not.

387
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,680
We’re friends.

388
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,240
I’m totally chill about it.

389
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:10,880
Is that so?

390
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:12,040
Yeah.

391
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,440
I’m totally chill too.

392
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:29,200
Is it true what they say...

393
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:30,560
...that you can never
forget your first kiss?

394
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:33,040
Uh, Kree...

395
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:36,000
...but I’m probably
not your first kiss, am I?

396
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,040
Oh...

397
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:40,680
When you say it like that,
it makes me feel bad.

398
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:43,120
Oh, I'm sorry.

399
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:45,120
I didn't mean it like that.

400
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:50,160
Stop it!

401
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:51,200
That's enough, Kree.

402
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:53,040
I don't mind.

403
00:19:54,240 --> 00:19:56,840
I’ve never felt this happy before.

404
00:19:57,760 --> 00:20:00,480
But happiness usually
doesn't stay with us for long, you know.

405
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:04,200
And are you happy just like I am?

406
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:06,920
Yes, I am.

407
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:08,080
Really?

408
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:13,360
But all the happiness
that happened here...

409
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:15,000
...once we go back...

410
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,200
...we will probably have to turn it...

411
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:20,160
...into just a good memory.

412
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:24,480
What do you mean by that?

413
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:28,040
I mean everything that happened here...

414
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:30,240
...stays here.

415
00:20:35,520 --> 00:20:37,600
Look at that face you're making.

416
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:41,280
I'm sorry, Kree.

417
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:44,120
And one day, you’ll understand.

418
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,680
The plane is almost here.

419
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:14,120
We are landing in 15 minutes.

420
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:15,160
Whoa.

421
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:17,080
Talk about short notice.

422
00:21:17,080 --> 00:21:18,840
Coming and going as she pleases.

423
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:20,200
What a heartless woman!

424
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:25,800
Everyone, wake up, wake up!

425
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:28,120
Hey, boy.

426
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,280
What now?

427
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:31,520
No more surprises, please.
I'm done.

428
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:32,720
The plane...

429
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:35,160
...is coming to pick us up in 15 minutes.

430
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:35,800
Really?

431
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:39,800
Yay! I’m so happy!

432
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:44,000
Wait, why is she
the only one celebrating?

433
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:56,200
I'm feeling a bit sad.

434
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:58,560
I’m gonna miss this place so much.

435
00:21:58,560 --> 00:22:01,440
Goodbye,
Bear-Eared Mushroom.

436
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:04,520
Over here! Over here!

437
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:05,600
Over here! Come pick me up too!

438
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:07,240
Over here!

439
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:10,480
Dear passengers...

440
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:13,640
Glamorous Airline is here
to take everyone back home!

441
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:15,320
Today, our captain...

442
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:18,200
...came to welcome
all passengers back home...

443
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:20,200
Don't tell me...

444
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:25,400
Hello.

445
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,760
Hello, Khun Glam.

446
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:28,480
Hello, everyone.

447
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:32,000
Hello to every living soul
on Mushroom-Ear-Bear Island.

448
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:57,040
Thanks to every living soul
on Mushroom-Ear-Bear Island...

449
00:22:57,040 --> 00:23:00,920
...for making such
a powerful noise to welcome me.

450
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:02,080
The Mushroom-Ear-Bear is deeply honored...

451
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:03,200
...to welcome Khun Glam.

452
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,720
The most legendary,
adorable bear...

453
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,160
...that everyone must meet at least once.

454
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,840
Thank you, Mushroom-Ear-Bear...

455
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:08,840
Bear-Eared Mushroom.

456
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,240
...on Mushroom-Ear-Bear Island...

457
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:13,400
...for keeping the cabin crew
of Glamorous Airline...

458
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:16,440
...safe and sound until today.

459
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:17,560
Keeping us safe?

460
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:19,480
That thing almost ripped
my guts out in the first place!

461
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:23,080
Hey, it's a happy ending,
don't bring up the past.

462
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:24,680
Ms. Petchgam Ploy...

463
00:23:24,680 --> 00:23:27,400
...I’d like to have a word with you
in private later.

464
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:28,800
Understood.

465
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:29,640
Khun Glam...

466
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:33,960
...Ms. Petchgam Ploy is
a really good supervisor, you know.

467
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:42,520
Do you realize what things
you did that were not professional...

468
00:23:42,520 --> 00:23:44,520
