Kree looks charming...

519
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:57,880
...and attractive with a mustache.

520
00:25:57,880 --> 00:25:59,320
I think right now...

521
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:02,040
...anyone who has a grudge
against that Petchgam Ploy...

522
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:03,080
...the time has come.

523
00:26:03,080 --> 00:26:05,120
Should we order her
to hunt wild boars for us to eat?

524
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:06,040
Great!

525
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:07,760
Hey, or...

526
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:11,080
should we make her clean up
our poop and pee?

527
00:26:11,080 --> 00:26:11,920
It's fine.

528
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:13,760
I'm not angry at any of you.

529
00:26:13,760 --> 00:26:16,080
I just want to clarify
so everyone knows that...

530
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:17,360
...Mr. Kreetha and I...

531
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:19,840
...have nothing going on
like you all gossiped about.

532
00:26:19,840 --> 00:26:21,320
Right, Mr. Kreetha?

533
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:23,160
Uh, yes, that's right.

534
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:23,920
It might have been the effects...

535
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:27,920
...of consuming raw Bear-Eared Mushrooms.

536
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:29,640
It caused a loss of sanity...

537
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:31,800
...and led to some strange behaviors.

538
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:33,680
Uh, yes, yes.
That's right.

539
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:35,160
Yes, raw Bear-Eared Mushrooms...

540
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:37,200
...must have made us high.

541
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:39,840
Please don't take it seriously.

542
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:40,760
Alright.

543
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:43,400
In that case,
let's set it to zero.

544
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:46,200
Let's all have a fresh start, everyone.

545
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:47,480
Great!
Yes, yes, that's great!

546
00:26:47,480 --> 00:26:48,840
For everyone else...

547
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:51,560
...it's like starting fresh every day.

548
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:54,480
But for me, it has finally arrived.

549
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:56,520
My very last flight.

550
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:59,280
Ms. Petchgam Ploy,
please go ahead and rest inside.

551
00:26:59,280 --> 00:27:01,280
Doctor Yep, after you.

552
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:10,040
If during the farewell...

553
00:27:10,040 --> 00:27:13,040
...anyone gets so deeply touched
that you can't hold back...

554
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:14,600
...you can cry right away.

555
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:17,840
It's not gonna be touching
the moment you tell me to cry.

556
00:27:17,840 --> 00:27:19,560
Which camera should I look at, Doctor?

557
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:20,880
Camera four.

558
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,000
Okay.

559
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:31,640
Thank you, Glamorous Airline,
for hiring me...

560
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,200
...to work here.

561
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:35,680
Thank you, Khun Glam...

562
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:37,440
...and Ms. Petchgam Ploy...

563
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:39,800
...for taking me in like a daughter...

564
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:40,880
...and letting me earn my wings...

565
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:42,760
...as a beautiful angel.

566
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:44,760
If you want to clap,
you can clap now.

567
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,840
Lastly...

568
00:27:49,840 --> 00:27:51,280
...Chai...

569
00:27:51,280 --> 00:27:52,840
...Tid-Gift...

570
00:27:52,840 --> 00:27:55,560
...Sky...

571
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:57,000
...Kreetha...

572
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:58,000
...All-New...

573
00:27:58,000 --> 00:27:59,920
...thank you for the friendship.

574
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:02,400
I will remember it
for the rest of my life.

575
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:03,560
I want everyone...

576
00:28:03,560 --> 00:28:05,280
...to remember this name.

577
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:07,720
Glamorous Airline's angel
of everyone...

578
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:08,640
...Chaba...

579
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:09,960
...Bacara...

580
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,520
...Scott Penis.

581
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:12,360
Everyone...

582
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,200
...let's say this name together...

583
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:16,880
...to praise Chaba.

584
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:20,880
Chaba Bacara Scott Penis...

585
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:23,240
Applause, please!

586
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,160
Keep saying it.

587
00:28:25,880 --> 00:28:27,880
You can scream now!

588
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:31,320
I'm not screaming for you.

589
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:32,000
Why?

590
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:33,920
I'm screaming
because I’m happy to go home!

591
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:36,440
The plane is so small,
why don't we find something to do?

592
00:28:36,440 --> 00:28:37,440
You're getting on my nerves!

593
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:47,080
Once we land,
I’ll definitely have to go get a massage.

594
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:48,120
Would you like me
to give you a massage?

595
00:28:48,120 --> 00:28:49,960
Oh, Mr. Kreetha!

596
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:51,280
When did you come in?

597
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:53,080
Do you have any idea
how rude this is?

598
00:28:54,120 --> 00:28:56,480
Keep it down, please.
Don't be so loud.

599
00:28:56,480 --> 00:28:58,120
Everyone else is going to hear us.

600
00:28:58,120 --> 00:29:00,160
Get out now.
That is an order.

601
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:05,200
As a cabin crew member,
I respect you.

602
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:06,520
Then get out!

603
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:10,360
But as a man...

604
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:11,920
...I like you.

605
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:18,280
Do you understand
the meaning of setting it to zero?

606
00:29:18,280 --> 00:29:22,040
Ms. Petchgam Ploy, you can set
whatever you want back to zero...

607
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:25,920
...but I can't set my heart back
to zero anymore.

608
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:27,920
But it is against airline regulations.

609
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:37,680
Ah, here it is.
The Employee Heart Protection Regulation.

610
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:39,960
The second line states that...

611
00:29:40,360 --> 00:29:41,720
...when out of uniform...

612
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:44,880
...all employees shall have the right...

613
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:48,280
to follow the calling of their own hearts.

614
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:51,400
And what are you going to do?

615
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:56,600
Move forward and pursue you...

616
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:58,440
...until you accept my love.

617
00:30:02,280 --> 00:30:05,240
Line number two,
Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

618
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:08,480
You stubborn boy!

619
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:18,520
What kind of snake is the cutest?

620
00:30:19,120 --> 00:30:21,280
What kind of snake is the cutest?

621
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:25,840
A snakey, snakey...

622
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:28,000
What kind of snake feels guilty?

623
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:30,280
What kind of snake feels guilty?

624
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:34,880
A snake cheating on the test...

625
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:37,600
I'm sorry, teacher, I won't cheat anymore!

626
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:40,000
What kind of snake is great
at playing musical instruments?

627
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:41,080
Snake...

628
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:42,480
A Gong-playing snake!

629
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:43,960
That’s supposed to be "Ngu Keng-Kong"
(The Mythical Medusa Snake)!

630
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:45,280
Yikes! You're right!

631
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:50,840
Then what kind of snake
follows us everywhere?

632
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:53,360
The "Ngu-Kao" snake...
"Ngoa-Ku" (My shadow)!

633
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:56,200
Correct! Wow, you're good.

634
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:58,240
What kind of snake cannot have kids?

635
00:30:58,240 --> 00:31:00,920
A "burnt-wiener" pit viper.

636
00:31:00,920 --> 00:31:02,920
Right? Thanks, buddy.

637
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:08,160
Help! Help!

638
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:09,680
Holy shit!

639
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:14,600
If the bottle points to someone,
that person has to...

640
00:31:15,120 --> 00:31:16,280
Are you hungry?

641
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:19,040
You just won't stop
eating the prop food.

642
00:31:19,040 --> 00:31:23,080
Turn around and kiss the cheek
of the person on your left.

643
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:31,320
Kiss her! Kiss her! Kiss her!

644
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:34,440
Chai, I got this. I got this.

645
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:35,320
Got what?

646
00:31:35,320 --> 00:31:37,000
The kissing, no, wait,
how should I kiss?

647
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:39,440
You have to refuse first!

648
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:40,520
Oh, really?

649
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:44,520
I can't do that.
It's disrespectful to her.

650
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:56,960
You laughed!
Why did you laugh?

651
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:57,960
But we got the shot, right?

652
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:01,320
The reason I could speak to that snake...

653
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:02,760
...is because I...Bear-Eared Mushroom.

654
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:05,160
"...because I ate the Bear-Eared Mushroom."

655
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,120
Let's do that again.

656
00:32:06,120 --> 00:32:07,960
The reason I could speak to that snake...

657
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:10,400
...is because...the Bear-Eared Mushroom.

658
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:13,560
What was it again?

659
00:32:13,920 --> 00:32:15,600
"...because I ate the Bear-Eared Mushroom."

660
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,200
Okay.

661
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:18,720
Bear-Eared Mushroom.

662
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:19,720
Holding this pose is so tiring.

663
00:32:20,160 --> 00:32:24,040
Listen, you two ate way
too many mushrooms...

664
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:25,000
...and now you're hallucinating.

665
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:27,120
Watch out or you'll go to a house
before you get a boyfriend.

666
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:28,440
Oh, sorry!
Go crazy! Sorry!

667
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:31,880
What? Where are you running off to?
Come do it with us!

668
00:32:31,880 --> 00:32:33,200
Wait, what?

669
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:34,640
All-New, wait.

670
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:35,600
Hey!

671
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:36,400
Come here.

672
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:37,880
Don't mess with me.

673
00:32:40,280 --> 00:32:42,240
Come on!

674
00:32:42,240 --> 00:32:44,720
Come on,
come dance with me first!

675
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:46,960
Hey,
where are you going, All-New?

676
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:49,280
Come dance first!

677
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:51,120
Get over here!

678
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:55,520
You can't leave!

679
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:58,880
Are you sure this is just vitamins?

680
00:32:58,880 --> 00:33:00,680
You seriously look like
Sun Wukong, for real.

681
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:02,240
Well, you're the one
who made me hold it.

682
00:33:02,240 --> 00:33:03,440
Why didn't you
make a bamboo Betong stick?

683
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:06,160
It's not about the stick,
it's about your face!

684
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:08,760
And the director...

685
00:33:08,760 --> 00:33:11,120
...he just sat there laughing
and wouldn't call a cut!

686
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:12,120
I'm exhausted, dammit!

687
00:33:15,280 --> 00:33:16,520
I need some advice.

688
00:33:16,520 --> 00:33:17,640
Well, a friend of mine...

689
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:20,160
...ended up sleeping
with her close friend.

690
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:21,760
And now they're scared
everything will change.

691
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:23,160
If you were them,
what would you do?

692
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:26,160
Don't tell me something happened
on the island that night.

693
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:28,440
Who is that?

694
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:30,160
Our VIP passenger for this flight.

695
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:31,280
Hello, Ms. Mintra.

696
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:31,920
Who is she?

697
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:33,920
Her name is Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

698
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:34,800
Cute...

699
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:35,880
Thank you.

700
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:37,000
Not you.

701
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:38,240
Excuse me...

702
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:39,240
Is she hitting on her?
